es commissioned for the Phil Spector box set and a spirited discussion with Peter Buck of R.E.M. about rock criticism, for example-DeCurtis also ventures with insight and power beyond the world of rock & roll. A joint profile of the political writers Neil Sheehan and Taylor Branch and provocative looks at the work of novelists Don DeLillo and T. Coraghessan Boyle round out this eclectic collection.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Rock.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999z978311071360240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822397922zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822397922423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780822397922/original  a978-3-11-071360-2  Duke University Press Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999c1964d1999  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles